        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          Good gameplan from Emery and followed through well by the majority of the players for the majority of the game. We largely nullified Kane via marking-in-numbers, defended well in the defensive third (Sokratis and Monreal exceptional, Leno with a ridiculous save from Sissoko) and counter-attacked successfully on a few occasions. I was initially furious about the offside/penalty but on the balance of decisions, we were also very lucky with Aubameyang's penalty and Xhaka's challenge on Kane. I can understand why the ref missed it in real time but I thought it was a (standard) foul for a tackle from behind 'live'. It's impossible to say what the result would have been had every big decision been awarded correctly, but we'd likely have been playing with 10 men for 78 minutes of the game so just a warning for fellow Gooners who are bemoaning not having VAR this season. I would like it to be implemented though since officiating a sport is, at times, an impossible task for 3 humans.
